<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Mary Elizabeth Cooley was an instructor in geology at Mt. Holyoke College. She later became assistant to the director of the Hopwood Awards program at the University of Michigan.</p>
</bioghist>


<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The collection consists of correspondence relating to her research into the life and career of American admiral and explorer, Charles Wilkes. There are also papers concerning her father, sociologist, Charles Horton Cooley. Some of her correspondents include William H. Hobbs, Vilhjalmur Stefansson, and Dorothy Tyler.</p>
</scopecontent>

